Package source.user

Class Student

java.lang.Object
source.user.User
source.user.Student
All Implemented Interfaces:
ICampParticipant
public class Student extends User implements ICampParticipant
Represents a student. A student is a user (inheritance), and can have campCommittee and campAttendee roles (composition)
Since:
2023-11-10

    • registerForCamp

      public void registerForCamp(String campName, boolean committeeRole)
      Register for a camp. This method calls CampManager.addParticipantToCamp() to do the actual registration.

      Corresponding exception will be thrown if there is any error. No exceptions means student is sucessfully registered.

      Specified by:
      registerForCamp in interface ICampParticipant
      Parameters:
      campName - Name of the camp.
      committeeRole - True for committee, false for attendee.
      Throws:
      MultipleCommitteeRoleException
      CampNotFoundException
      InvalidUserGroupException
      DateClashException
      DeadlineOverException
      CampFullException
      WithdrawnException
